Privacy Policy for ScrollerCat extension submitted to Chrome Web Store

Effective Date: 2024.08.24

ScrollerCat is committed to protecting privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, 
use, and safeguard your information when you use the extension.

1. Information We Collect
  1.1. Personal Information:
    Screenshots: The Extension captures screenshots of your active browser tab when you initiate a screenshot capture. 
    These screenshots are used only for the purpose of the Extensionâ€™s functionality and are not stored or transmitted to any external servers.

    Tool settings: Settings such as font-size or scroll speed are saved locally. These are deleted when browser history is deleted. Settings
    are only used for the purpose of the Extension's functionality and are not stored or transmitted externally.

2. How We Use Information
  2.1. Providing and Improving the Extension:
    We use the collected information to operate and enhance the Extension's functionality, including injecting scripts and capturing visible tabs.
  2.2. User Support:
    If you contact us for support, we may use the information you provide to assist you.

3. Information Sharing and Disclosure
  3.1. No Third-Party Sharing:
    We do not share your personal information with third parties.
  3.2. Legal Requirements:
    We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g., a court or a government agency).

4. Data Security
  4.1. Security Measures:
    We implement appropriate technical measures to protect your information against accidental alteration, unauthorized disclosure, or access.

5. Changes to This Privacy Policy
  5.1. Updates:
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Refer to the GitHub repository for changes (https://github.com/JLobbes/scrollerCat/new/main).

6. Contact Us
    If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact me at scrollerCat@gmail.com
